(incomplete)

== Postgres setup ==
pg_hba.conf - allow from gladd server

From a fresh postgres setup (ie no existing gladbooks database)

Create the gladd user:
# su - postgres
# postgres:~$ psql
postgres=# CREATE ROLE dba WITH SUPERUSER NOINHERIT;
> CREATE ROLE
postgres=# CREATE user gladd;
> CREATE ROLE
postgres=# GRANT dba TO gladd;
> GRANT ROLE
postgres=# ALTER USER gladd CREATEDB;
> ALTER ROLE
postgres=#\q
postgres:~$ exit

Added the demo database:
# su - gladd
$ cd /usr/local/gladd/gladbooks-ui/sql
$ make dropdb
$ make all
$ make demo

== Reset the db ==
# su - postgres
# psql
postgres=# drop database gladbooks;
postgres=# drop user gladbooks;
postgres=# drop user gladd;


This allows the user to create the c language functions.
